    <briefdescription>
<para>Real-to-complex halfband 2:1 decimator (Architecture D2). </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Lifted from dp_hbdecim_r2cf32_t (c/src/hbdecim.c). Accepts real float32 input and produces CF32 IQ at half the input rate, with an embedded fs/4 frequency shift (same effect as mixing with e^{jπn/2} before decimating, at zero extra multiplications).</para>
<para>The output at sample m is: y(m) = (FIR(even) + j·delay(odd)) · (-1)^m</para>
<para>where the sign pattern (-1)^m provides the fs/4 shift correction.</para>
<para>Lifecycle: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="hbdecim__r2c__core_8h_1ae2f61225436b203a1fb8382e3f23a13c" kindref="member">hbdecim_r2c_state_t</ref><sp/>*r<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="hbdecim__r2c__core_8h_1af2b134c8acb2d0c191af67ef14676630" kindref="member">hbdecim_r2c_create</ref>(num_taps,<sp/>h);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="keywordtype">size_t</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>n<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="hbdecim__r2c__core_8h_1a720623c3d246990fab8b428c20021669" kindref="member">hbdecim_r2c_execute</ref>(r,<sp/>in,<sp/>num_in,<sp/>out,<sp/>max_out);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="hbdecim__r2c__core_8h_1a29a65323f3df7c8cb289fe1bb9b85646" kindref="member">hbdecim_r2c_destroy</ref>(r);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
